        <span>About</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Built by a practitioner.<br><em>For practitioners.</em></h1>
      <p class=3D"hero-sub">NEXUS EOC was designed from the ground up by an=
 emergency management professional with nearly 25 years of operational expe=
rience across disaster response, remote sensing, WMD consequence management=
, and national-level continuity operations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class=3D"rule"></div>

    <main>
      <div>
        <div class=3D"about-block">
          <div class=3D"section-label">About the Developer</div>
          <p>Nicholas Edwards is a Lieutenant Colonel in the California Air=
 National Guard and an emergency management professional currently completi=
ng a Master of Science in Emergency Management at the University of Souther=
n California. He is a Certified Business Continuity Professional (CBCP) thr=
ough DRI International and a member of the National Emergency Management As=
sociation (NEMA).</p>
          <p>His career spans nearly 25 years of active and reserve militar=
y service across intelligence, ISR operations, WMD consequence management, =
and all-hazards disaster response. He has served as a Remote Sensing Coordi=
nator at Joint Command Posts during major wildfire incidents, commanded a f=
ederally certified WMD Civil Support Team responsible for CBRN reconnaissan=
ce and consequence management across California, and led national-level ope=
rations teams delivering real-time situational awareness to senior DoD and =
interagency leadership across all 54 states and territories.</p>
          <p>Edwards served as National Program Manager of FireGuard, a rem=
ote sensing and geospatial intelligence capability built in response to the=
 2018 Camp Fire and scaled to support CAL FIRE, FEMA, and state Emergency O=
perations Centers during major disasters. He has trained emergency managers=
 at the national, state, and local level and taught incident awareness and =
assessment courses across the country.</p>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"about-block">
          <div class=3D"section-label">Credentials &amp; Background</div>
          <div class=3D"cred-grid">
            <div class=3D"cred-item">
              <div class=3D"cred-icon">=F0=9F=8E=93</div>
