                <div class=3D"cred-title">All-Hazards Disaster Response =E2=
=80=94 Wildfires, Hurricanes, WMD, Public Health</div>
                <div class=3D"cred-desc">Deployed in support of wildfires, =
civil unrest, and public health emergencies. Coordinated interagency respon=
se across federal, state, and tribal partners. FEMA ICS 100/200/300/400 cer=
tified.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class=3D"cred-item">
              <div class=3D"cred-icon">=F0=9F=8F=9B</div>
              <div class=3D"cred-text">
                <div class=3D"cred-title">Member =E2=80=94 National Emergen=
cy Management Association (NEMA)</div>
                <div class=3D"cred-desc">Professional association represent=
ing state and territory emergency management directors and senior practitio=
ners across the United States.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class=3D"cred-item">
              <div class=3D"cred-icon">=F0=9F=94=92</div>
              <div class=3D"cred-text">
                <div class=3D"cred-title">Active Federal Security Clearance=
</div>
                <div class=3D"cred-desc">Available for engagements requirin=
g cleared personnel. Extensive experience in classified operations, NC3, an=
d sensitive national security programs.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class=3D"platform-block">
          <div class=3D"section-label">About NEXUS EOC</div>
          <p>NEXUS EOC is a web-based emergency management training simulat=
or that generates a unique, geographically accurate scenario for every sess=
ion based on the selected incident type and jurisdiction. An AI engine eval=
uates player decisions against NIMS, ICS, ESF, and FEMA doctrine in real ti=
me, then delivers a comprehensive after-action review calibrated to the pla=
yer's role and jurisdiction when they type ENDEX.</p>
          <p>The platform supports 23 roles =E2=80=94 including EOC Directo=
r, all four Section Chiefs, PIO, Safety Officer, and all 15 Emergency Suppo=
rt Function Liaison Officers =E2=80=94 and six jurisdiction types from Rura=
l County to Tribal Nation. Every session is different. No facilitator requi=
red.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

